## Chatbot API
A Django-based RESTful API for interacting with a chatbot. The chatbot is powered by a transformer-based language model.

Table of Contents
Installation
Usage
API Endpoints
Testing with Postman
Documentation

## Installation
To set up the Chatbot API on your local machine:

Clone the repository using the link to your GitHub repository.
Navigate to the project directory named "ChatbotAPI".
Install the required packages using pip with the requirements file.
Set up the database by running the Django migrations.
Start the development server using the Django management command.
Usage
After setting up, visit http://127.0.0.1:8000/ in your browser to access the API and its documentation.

## API Endpoints
The API provides the following main endpoints:

A POST endpoint at http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/chat/ to send a message to the chatbot.
A GET endpoint at http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/chat/history/ to retrieve chat history.
Testing with Postman
For ease of testing, a Postman collection has been provided:

## Download and install Postman from their official website.
In the root directory of the project, locate the Postman collection file named "Chatbot API.postman_collection.json".
Import this file into Postman.
You can now start sending requests to understand and test the API endpoints.

## Documentation
Detailed API documentation is available. For an interactive experience:

Visit the Swagger UI at http://127.0.0.1:8000/swagger/.
Alternatively, access the ReDoc UI at http://127.0.0.1:8000/redoc/.
